<item>
            <title>[WICKET-3648] AbstractMarkupParser.removeComment() goes in endless loop when the comment is multi line</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3648</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A markup like:&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;!--&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;if lt IE 8 &amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;style&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/style&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;script src=&quot;js/ie7.js&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;!&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;endif&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;--&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and the application is configured with: getMarkupSettings().setStripComments(true);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;makes AbstractMarkupParser#removeComment(String) to enter in endless loop.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12505302">WICKET-3648</key>
            <summary>AbstractMarkupParser.removeComment() goes in endless loop when the comment is multi line</summary>
