                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13025776" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2011 12:54:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&#1058;he problem is that there is an inner tag and the RawMarkup for the opening comment has no knowledge about the closing tag.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025780" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2011 13:16:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a unit test demonstrating the problem:&lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.wicket.markup.MarkupParserTest.wicket3648testCommentsWithNestedElements()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remove the prefix &quot;wicket3648&quot; to run it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025801" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2011 14:20:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A patch fixing the problem.&lt;br/&gt;
Please review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025808" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2011 14:35:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This specific bug is fixed but stripping comments causes IE conditional comments to become broken/cut.&lt;br/&gt;
It would be good to test &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3433&quot; title=&quot;Wicket parses HTML inside IE conditional comments&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-3433&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-3433&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with getMarkupSettings().setStripComments(true);&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025821" author="mgrigorov" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2011 14:52:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Link with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3500&quot; title=&quot;Method AbstractMarkupParser.removeComment() causes an endless loop&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-3500&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-3500&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Seems to be the very same problem. It has been fixed only in 1.4.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13026319" author="mgrigorov" created="Thu, 28 Apr 2011 14:25:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed with r1097472.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
